(footprint "B3F-3152"
	(layer "F.Cu")
	(descr "6mm tactile switch, right angle (Omron B3F-3152, Mouser 653-B3F-3152). No official KiCad footprint matches this part's real geometry (the community Button_Switch_THT:SW_SPST_Omron_B3F-315x_Angled footprint has its ground/mounting-leg pads on the opposite side vs. this part's real datasheet/manufacturer geometry - verified: only this manufacturer-sourced geometry reconciles with the board's existing copper via a plain rotation, no mirror). Geometry sourced from the manufacturer's own KiCad library export (SamacSys/Ultra Librarian). Ground/mounting-leg pads renamed from the manufacturer's numbered '3'/'4' to 'GND' (duplicate pad name) to match the project's schematic symbol pin. Includes the manufacturer's STEP 3D model.")
	(tags "Switch Tactile 6mm Right Angle B3F-3152 Omron")
	(property "Reference" "REF**"
		(at 2.25 1.075 0)
		(layer "F.SilkS")
		(hide yes)
		(effects
